After having investigated, I finally found why we got the error while running the Ant script file...

First, I had to disable the trace filter while running the JUnit task (filtertrace="off" in the new attached build.xml)

Second, looking at the stack trace:
java.lang.ClassCastException: [Ljava.lang.Class; incompatible with junit.framework.Test
	at org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.JUnitTestRunner.run(JUnitTestRunner.java:400)
	at org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.JUnitTestRunner.launch(JUnitTestRunner.java:1063)
	at org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.JUnitTestRunner.main(JUnitTestRunner.java:914)
I got the corresponding JUnitTestRunner.java source file and look at line 400 (in bold below):
                // check for a static suite method first, even when using
                // JUnit 4
                Method suiteMethod = null;
                if (!testMethodsSpecified) {
                try {
                    // check if there is a suite method
                    suiteMethod = testClass.getMethod("suite", new Class[0]);
                } catch (NoSuchMethodException e) {
                    // no appropriate suite method found. We don't report any
                    // error here since it might be perfectly normal.
                }
                }
                if (suiteMethod != null) {
                    // if there is a suite method available, then try
                    // to extract the suite from it. If there is an error
                    // here it will be caught below and reported.
                    suite = (Test) suiteMethod.invoke(null, new Object[0]);
                } else {
Hence, it appears that the JUnit test runner is looking for a suite() static method in the run class. If it exists, it's expecting it to return a Test.

Last, looking at DynamicSuiteBuilder, this class has a static method suite() which returns Class<?>[]...
Which explains the ClassCastException!

HTH

I have a resource class with the following annotated property:

@OslcPropertyDefinition("http:/purl.org/dc/terms/aBoolean")
