We need a way to specify all the RDF types of an extended resource dynamically. However, a RDF type equal to the resource class name is always added to the resource if the annotation @OslcName is not specified in the resource class.
The default RDF type (class name) should be added to an extended resource only if no type was added to the resource via method setTypes(Collection<URI> type). For example, the crtv:ComputerSystem type in the payload below should be specified via setTypes method (and no http://jazz.net/ns/ism/registry#ReconciledResource RDF type should be added to it):
@OslcNamespace("http://jazz.net/ns/ism/registry#") @OslcResourceShape(title = "Resource Record", describes = "http://jazz.net/ns/ism/registry#ResourceRecord") public class ReconciledResource extends AbstractResource { ... }
<rdf:RDF> <crtv:ComputerSystem rdf:about = "http://server:9080/oslc/resources/1378826668659"> <oslc:domain rdf:resource = "http://jazz.net/ns/ism/registry#"/> <oslc:serviceProvider rdf:resource = "http://server:9080/oslc/rr"/> <crtv:systemBoardUUID>avcd1b2728-3013-c8f3-64db-c74bd38ca7e3f4</crtv:systemBoardUUID> <crtv:manufacturer>IBM</crtv:manufacturer> <oslc:shortTitle rdf:parseType = "Literal">a1.2.3.4-4</oslc:shortTitle> <crtv:serialNumber>LG3G44</crtv:serialNumber> <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource = "http://productinstance.ibm.com/devices/productSourceToken-1-4"/> <crtv:model>2007CAO</crtv:model> </crtv:ComputerSystem> </rdf:RDF>

