The method
    getResource(final URI namedGraphUri, final URI resourceUri, final Class<T> clazz)

has a return of
   getResourcesFromModel(model, clazz).get(0);

This will fail if the array is empty.


Change so that the method handles this exception. Something like ...

        List<T> resourcesFromModel = getResourcesFromModel(model, clazz);
        if (resourcesFromModel.isEmpty())
		return null;
        return resourcesFromModel.get(0);

Unfortunately Rational DOORS Next Generation (RDNG) can only consume RDF/XML-ABBREV, regardless of the Accept header it might send. The Accept header could be application/xml in which case OSLC4J will send RDF/XML-ABBREV. But there are cases where RDNG uses Accept=application/rdf+xml for accessing ServiceProvider resources, but cannot consume the resulting RDF/XML.

A system property:
org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.alwaysXMLAbbrevOnlyProviders

Should be added, and the following code added to org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.provider.jena AbstractOslcRdfXmlProvider.java:

		String serializationLanguage = getSerializationLanguage(baseMediaType);

		// This is a special case to handle RDNG GET on a ServiceProvider resource.
		// RDNG can only consume RDF/XML-ABBREV, regardless of what it sends in the Accept header
		// The org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.alwaysXMLAbbrevOnlyProviders system property ise used
		// to turn off this special case
		if ((objects != null && objects[0] != null) &&
			( objects[0] instanceof ServiceProviderCatalog || objects[0] instanceof ServiceProvider ) &&
			"true".equals(System.getProperty("org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.alwaysXMLAbbrevOnlyProviders")) ) {
			serializationLanguage = FileUtils.langXMLAbbrev;
		}

		try
...

Then OSLC4J apps that need to interact with RDNG can set org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.alwaysXMLAbbrevOnlyProviders to true to effect this behavior.

This is described in Defect 115412 (https://jazz.net/jazz03/web/projects/Requirements%20Management#action=com.ibm.team.workitem.viewWorkItem&id=115412)

The getValues() method in org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.core.model.AllowedValues fails with a cast exception if there is only a single allowed value.

The code should be as follows to handle both zero, one, or more allowed values:

    public Collection<?> getValues()
    {
        Object o = getExtendedProperties().get(PROPERTY_ALLOWED_VALUE);
        if (o == null)
        {
            return Collections.emptyList();
        }
        else if (o instanceof Collection)
        {
            return (Collection<?>)o;
        }
        else
        {
            return Collections.singleton(o);
        }
    }

How did you end up with a non-Collection value anyway?

The method below has the following signature:


public void setValues(final Collection<? extends Object> values) {
    getExtendedProperties().put(PROPERTY_ALLOWED_VALUE, values);
}

You can't pass anything but a collection there. Did you call getExtendedProperties() and modify it in a dirty way somewhere else?

The non-collection value was put there by Lyo when reading a shape resource using fromJenaModel:

   // Read the entire RDF from the creation factory shape reference
   Model rdfModel = ModelFactory.createDefaultModel();
   rdfModel.read(connection.getResource(base,InputStream.class), base);

   // Find all resource shapes in that RDF -there can be more than one
   ResourceShape[] shapes = (ResourceShape[])
      JenaModelHelper.fromJenaModel(rdfModel,ResourceShape.class);

We need to fix this:

    try {
        return ImmutableList.copyOf((RdfsClass[]) JenaModelHelper
                .fromJenaModel(model, RdfsClass.class));
    } catch (IllegalAccessException | IllegalArgumentException
            | InstantiationException | InvocationTargetException
            | SecurityException | NoSuchMethodException
            | DatatypeConfigurationException | OslcCoreApplicationException
            | URISyntaxException e) {
        throw new IllegalStateException(e);
    }

I would suggest to reduce it just to three kinds of exceptions:

- checked bad input exception: URISyntaxException and maybe OslcCoreApplicationException. This means the RDF Model had some bad input. Developers need to check it at the runtime before calling us.
- checked operation exception: InstantiationException, InvocationTargetException, IllegalArgumentException, NoSuchMethodException. These occur when Jena tries to do unmarshall RDF into a class instance and something blows up in the reflection stage. Developers shall unit test their code for this  likely annotations were wrong.
- unchecked else (wrap in a kind of RuntimeException): DatatypeConfigurationException, SecurityException. Some stuff on the JVM caused some crazy exception.

And what is OslcCoreApplicationException? There is no idea about the cause of it from the name, just the source.

When running on JVM with Turkish locale set, OSLC4J is not able to create rdf/xml or JSON representation of a ServiceProvider. Instead of that an OslcCoreInvalidPropertyDefinitionException is thrown with the message "OSLC004: Invalid property definition annotation http:\/\/open-services.net\/ns\/core#icon for method getIcon of class org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.core.model.Publisher"
It seems that Turkish dotless-I problem occurs here. Bug is caused by invoking java.lang.String.toLowerCase() without passing Locale.ENGLISH as an argument.
Proposal of the fix:
Change: final String lowercasedFirstCharacter = methodName.substring(startingIndex, endingIndex).toLowerCase();
to: final String lowercasedFirstCharacter = methodName.substring(startingIndex, endingIndex).toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);
in String getDefaultPropertyName(final Method method) method of JenaModelHelper (line 1510) and JsonHelper (line 834). The same method in ResourceShapeFactory (line 310) may also be error prone.

The following predicates are all out of date. We should update the samples to use ldp:membershipResource and ldp:hasMemberRelation. Also we should use a specific container type like ldp:DirectContainer instead of just ldp:Container.

/org.eclipse.lyo.ldp.sample.bugtracker/src/main/resources/bugTracker.ttl

@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix ldp:     <http://www.w3.org/ns/ldp#>.

<> a ldp:Container;
	ldp:membershipSubject <>;
