Net worth has a similar problem.

Code in org.eclipse.lyo.oslc4j.core.modelResourceShape can fail if a Property resource in a shape does not have the required oslc:propertyDefinition attribute.

The current code is:

	public void setProperties(final Property[] properties) {
		this.properties.clear();
		if (properties != null) {
			for(Property prop :properties) {
				this.properties.put(prop.getPropertyDefinition(), prop);
			}
		}
	}

IBM RQM bug https://jazz.net/jazz02/resource/itemName/com.ibm.team.workitem.WorkItem/162426 shows the tat least one tool produces resource shapes that cause the above code to fail with an NPE on the put, because prop.getPropertyDefinition() returns null. More defensive code would add a check, discarding invalid properties:

    public void setProperties(final Property[] properties) {
        this.properties.clear();
        if (properties != null) {
            for (Property prop : properties) {
                // Work around for defect https://jazz.net/jazz02/resource/itemName/com.ibm.team.workitem.WorkItem/162426
                URI propertyDefinition = prop.getPropertyDefinition();
		if (propertyDefinition != null) {
                    this.properties.put(propertyDefinition, prop);
                }
            }
        }
    }

