The instanceShape property set for resource has an extra / after OSLC4JUtils.getServletURI(). e.g., <oslc:instanceShape rdf:resource="https://localhost:9443/iotp/services//resourceShapes/iotDeviceType"/>
The web.xml specifies the servlet mapping which is typically: <servlet-mapping> <servlet-name>JAX-RS Servlet</servlet-name> <url-pattern>/services/*</url-pattern> </servlet-mapping>
ServletListner.contextInitialized() uses the servlet mapping to set the servletUrlPattern to " /services/".
ResourceShapeFactory.createResourceShape() simply concatenates the path components to create the URL for a resource's shape. The baseURI already ends in a / as calculated from the servletUriPattern. final URI about = new URI(baseURI + "/" + resourceShapesPath + "/" + resourceShapePath);
But it should use a UriBuilder to properly handle the path elements and avoid the double // after the baseURI. final URI about = UriBuilder.fromUri(baseURI).path(resourceShapesPath).path(resourceShapePath).build();
This is actually an eclipse/Lyo OSLC4J core bug.

Application class of a generated adaptor will put resources imported from another domain into the RESOURCE_SHAPE_PATH_TO_RESOURCE_CLASS_MAP

However, the imports were missing. So, in my case I had to add the following:

// Start of user code imports
import my.domain.MyDomainConstants;
// End of user code

Just to clarify, 'My' domain is defined in another model separate from the Toolchain model, in another project and then included in the toolchain modelling project by adding the domain model as a project dependency.

