SRP is violated in lyo.oslc4j.provider.jena.AbstractOslcRdfXmlProvider#readFrom and there is no way to retrieve the contained model before the JenaModelHelper is called:

final Model model = ModelFactory.createDefaultModel();

...

reader.read(model,
            inputStream,
            "");

return JenaModelHelper.fromJenaModel(model, type);

Ad-hoc solution:

public class ClientResponseModelReader {
    private final ClientResponse response;

    public ClientResponseModelReader(ClientResponse response) {
        this.response = response;
    }

    Model readModel() {
        Model m = ModelFactory.createDefaultModel();
        final InputStream entity = (InputStream) response.getEntity(InputStream.class);
        m.read(entity, "");
        return m;
    }
}

I spoke with the OSLC Core lead and he confirmed that XMLLiteral content does not have to contain start/end tags.  It just needs to be an XML fragment which includes plain or escaped strings.

